1) Get the code

	a) via AD-SVN
		svn co https://ad-svn.informatik.uni-freiburg.de/student-projects/matthias-hertel/paper <YOUR CODE DIRECTORY>
	b) via git
		git clone https://github.com/mostafa-mahmoud/tokenization-repair.git <YOUR CODE DIRECTORY>

2) Get the models and data

	a) If you are on your own machine, copy the models and data
		scp -r <SOME SERVER FROM THE AD LAB>:/nfs/students/matthias-hertel/tokenization-repair-paper <YOUR DUMP DIRECTORY>
	b) If you are on a machine from the lab, do nothing.

3) Build the Docker container
	
	1) go to the code directory
		a) if you got the code from git
			cd <YOUR CODE DIRECTORY>/matthias-hertel
		b) if you got the code from ad-svn
			cd <YOUR CODE DIRECTORY>
	
	2) build the container
		docker build -t tokenization-repair .
		(Use wharfer instead of docker if you are an a machine from the lab.)

4) Start the Docker container

	a) On your own machine
		docker run -it -v <YOUR DUMP DIRECTORY>:/external tokenization-repair
	b) On a machine from the lab
		docker run -it -v /nfs/students/matthias-hertel/tokenization-repair-paper:/external tokenization-repair

5) Inside the container, repair some tokens!

	a) make beam-search
	b) make iterative
	
	Wait until the model is loaded.
	When the input symbol (> ) appears, type a sentence with tokenization errors and press enter to get a correction.
